<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 8:04PM EDT  by NWS Buffalo</headline>
<description>...LOCALLY HEAVY DOWNPOURS IN NIAGARA AND ORLEANS COUNTIES THIS
EVENING...
Slow moving showers and thunderstorms will produce locally heavy
rainfall in Niagara and Orleans counties through 11 p.m. Rainfall
amounts will vary, with rainfall amounts in excess of 2 inches
possible at some locations. Heavy rainfall will cause ponding of
water on roadways, especially in urban areas or areas with poor
drainage. Motorists should slow down and be prepared for poor
visibility due to the heavy rain.
Remember, never drive across a flooded roadway since the water
may be deeper than it looks. Turn around, don`t drown.</description>
